@@ -0,0 +1,399 @@
+{
+ "cells": [
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "# NSD-Imagery data orientation\n",
+    "\n",
+    "This notebook is a guided tour of the **minimal project download**. It is deliberately descriptive: the goal is to understand the files, dimensions, units, trial structure, and ROI labels before implementing RSA.\n",
+    "\n",
+    "The central data relationship is:\n",
+    "\n",
+    "`behavior/design → beta index → 3-D voxel response → ROI mask → trial × voxel matrix`\n",
+    "\n",
+    "Memory rule: the HDF5 beta array stays on disk. We read selected voxels across events; we do **not** execute `h5['betas'][:]`."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 0. Environment\n",
+    "\n",
+    "No GPU, CUDA, PyTorch, FreeSurfer, or fMRI preprocessing package is needed for this notebook. The only less-standard dependencies are `h5py` (lazy HDF5 access) and `nibabel` (NIfTI/MGH files)."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "from pathlib import Path\n",
+    "import sys\n",
+    "\n",
+    "REPO_ROOT = Path.cwd().resolve()\n",
+    "if not (REPO_ROOT / 'nsdimagery').is_dir():\n",
+    "    REPO_ROOT = REPO_ROOT.parent\n",
+    "if not (REPO_ROOT / 'nsdimagery').is_dir():\n",
+    "    raise RuntimeError('Start Jupyter from the repository root or its notebooks/ directory.')\n",
+    "sys.path.insert(0, str(REPO_ROOT))\n",
+    "\n",
+    "import h5py\n",
+    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
+    "import nibabel as nib\n",
+    "import numpy as np\n",
+    "import pandas as pd\n",
+    "import seaborn as sns\n",
+    "from IPython.display import display\n",
+    "from PIL import Image\n",
+    "from scipy.io import loadmat\n",
+    "\n",
+    "from nsdimagery.io import (\n",
+    "    build_run_table, describe_hdf5, extract_masked_betas, find_data_root,\n",
+    "    infer_beta_layout, load_behavior, load_roi, paths_for_subject, read_ctab, validate_download,\n",
+    ")\n",
+    "\n",
+    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', context='notebook')\n",
+    "print('Python:', sys.version.split()[0])\n",
+    "print('Repository:', REPO_ROOT)"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 1. Locate and validate the download\n",
+    "\n",
+    "Your expected root is `REPO/data/nsd`. The manifest checks all eight subjects, all three volumetric masks, all beta files, and the 12 behavioral TSVs per subject."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "DATA_ROOT = find_data_root(REPO_ROOT)\n",
+    "print('Data root:', DATA_ROOT)\n",
+    "\n",
+    "manifest = validate_download(DATA_ROOT)\n",
+    "display(manifest)\n",
+    "assert manifest['ok'].all(), 'At least one expected file is absent.'\n",
+    "\n",
+    "print(f\"Total size covered by manifest: {manifest['size_MiB'].sum()/1024:.2f} GiB\")"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "### What each top-level folder means\n",
+    "\n",
+    "- `nsddata/experiments/nsdimagery`: task definitions, design matrices, cue pairs, and target images.\n",
+    "- `nsddata/bdata/nsdimagery`: what happened on each presented behavioral trial.\n",
+    "- `nsddata/ppdata/.../roi`: 3-D integer masks already aligned to each subject's 1.8-mm beta volume.\n",
+    "- `nsddata/freesurfer/.../label`: surface masks and color tables; in this project the color tables mainly tell us what the volumetric integer codes mean.\n",
+    "- `nsddata_betas`: the large estimated BOLD response amplitudes."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 2. Experimental and beta-block structure\n",
+    "\n",
+    "There are 12 acquired runs. Every run has 48 behavioral trials. Vision and imagery produce one beta per trial; attention produces two betas per trial (cue and detection epochs). Thus `9 × 48 + 3 × 96 = 720` beta volumes.\n",
+    "\n",
+    "The table below gives safe **run-level** slices. We will not infer the within-attention event mapping until inspecting the GLMsingle design."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "run_table = build_run_table()\n",
+    "display(run_table)\n",
+    "print('Behavioral trials:', run_table['n_behavior_trials'].sum())\n",
+    "print('Modeled beta events:', run_table['n_betas'].sum())"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 3. See the target stimuli\n",
+    "\n",
+    "Set A contains six geometric patterns. Set B contains five NSD natural scenes and one artwork. Set C is conceptual (`stripes → zebra → mammal`, `yellow → banana → fruit`) and therefore has no single fixed raw target image per concept."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "stim_root = DATA_ROOT / 'nsddata' / 'experiments' / 'nsdimagery' / 'rawtargetimages'\n",
+    "image_paths = sorted(stim_root.glob('set*/*.png'))\n",
+    "\n",
+    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 6, figsize=(16, 6))\n",
+    "for ax, path in zip(axes.flat, image_paths):\n",
+    "    ax.imshow(Image.open(path))\n",
+    "    ax.set_title(f'{path.parent.name}: {path.stem}', fontsize=8)\n",
+    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
+    "plt.tight_layout()"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 4. Behavioral TSVs: one row per presented trial\n",
+    "\n",
+    "Important columns include `CONDITION` (what was seen/attended/imagined), `CUE`, `FRAMEFILE`, `GROUNDTRUTH`, `BUTTON`, and timing/RT fields. In imagery, button 1 means vivid and button 2 means not vivid."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "SUBJECT = 1\n",
+    "behavior = load_behavior(DATA_ROOT, SUBJECT)\n",
+    "print('Shape:', behavior.shape)\n",
+    "print('Columns:')\n",
+    "print(list(behavior.columns))\n",
+    "display(behavior.head())\n",
+    "\n",
+    "run_order = run_table['run_name'].tolist()\n",
+    "trial_counts = behavior.groupby('RUN_NAME').size().reindex(run_order)\n",
+    "display(trial_counts.rename('behavioral rows').to_frame())\n",
+    "assert (trial_counts == 48).all()"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "imagery = behavior[behavior['RUN_NAME'].str.startswith('img')].copy()\n",
+    "imagery['BUTTON_NUMERIC'] = pd.to_numeric(imagery['BUTTON'], errors='coerce')\n",
+    "vividness = (\n",
+    "    imagery.groupby('RUN_NAME')['BUTTON_NUMERIC']\n",
+    "    .value_counts(dropna=False)\n",
+    "    .rename('n_trials')\n",
+    "    .reset_index()\n",
+    ")\n",
+    "display(vividness)\n",
+    "\n",
+    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
+    "sns.countplot(data=imagery, x='RUN_NAME', hue='BUTTON_NUMERIC', order=[r for r in run_order if r.startswith('img')], ax=ax)\n",
+    "ax.set_title('Imagery responses: button 1 = vivid, button 2 = not vivid')\n",
+    "ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)\n",
+    "plt.tight_layout()"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 5. MATLAB design files\n",
+    "\n",
+    "The run-level `*_dm.mat` files describe conditions over time. `designmatrixGLMsingle.mat` is the design actually used to obtain the 720 single-event betas. This cell inventories keys and shapes without presuming their internal organization."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "experiment_dir = DATA_ROOT / 'nsddata' / 'experiments' / 'nsdimagery'\n",
+    "\n",
+    "def mat_inventory(path):\n",
+    "    try:\n",
+    "        contents = loadmat(path, squeeze_me=True, struct_as_record=False)\n",
+    "        return pd.DataFrame([\n",
+    "            {'key': key, 'type': type(value).__name__, 'shape': getattr(value, 'shape', None)}\n",
+    "            for key, value in contents.items() if not key.startswith('__')\n",
+    "        ])\n",
+    "    except NotImplementedError:\n",
+    "        return describe_hdf5(path).rename(columns={'name': 'key'})\n",
+    "\n",
+    "for filename in ['visA_dm.mat', 'imgA_1_dm.mat', 'designmatrixGLMsingle.mat']:\n",
+    "    print('\\n', filename)\n",
+    "    display(mat_inventory(experiment_dir / filename))"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 6. HDF5 beta file: shape, chunks, and units\n",
+    "\n",
+    "The manual describes `/betas` in MATLAB order as `X × Y × Z × 720`. Because these files were written from MATLAB, **h5py normally exposes the same data as `720 × X × Y × Z`**. The code detects the layout rather than assuming an axis. Values are stored as `int16` after multiplying percent signal change by 300. Correct loading casts to floating point and divides by 300. The chunking is optimized for reading all events from a small number of voxels."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "subject_paths = paths_for_subject(DATA_ROOT, SUBJECT)\n",
+    "display(describe_hdf5(subject_paths['beta']))\n",
+    "\n",
+    "with h5py.File(subject_paths['beta'], 'r') as handle:\n",
+    "    beta_dataset = handle['betas']\n",
+    "    beta_shape = beta_dataset.shape\n",
+    "    print('Shape:', beta_shape)\n",
+    "    print('dtype:', beta_dataset.dtype)\n",
+    "    print('chunks:', beta_dataset.chunks)\n",
+    "    print('The event axis is the dimension of length 720; ROI shape verification comes next.')\n",
+    "    assert 720 in beta_shape"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 7. Volumetric ROI masks and label tables\n",
+    "\n",
+    "All three masks live in the same subject-native `func1pt8mm` grid as the beta data. `nsdgeneral` is binary. The other masks contain integer codes; the `.ctab` files translate codes into anatomical names. Values 0 (and sometimes −1) are not selected cortical ROIs."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "roi_arrays = {}\n",
+    "for roi_name in ['nsdgeneral', 'prf-visualrois', 'streams']:\n",
+    "    array, image = load_roi(DATA_ROOT, SUBJECT, roi_name)\n",
+    "    roi_arrays[roi_name] = array\n",
+    "    values, counts = np.unique(array, return_counts=True)\n",
+    "    summary = pd.DataFrame({'label': values, 'n_voxels': counts})\n",
+    "    print(f'\\n{roi_name}: shape={array.shape}, voxel sizes={image.header.get_zooms()[:3]}')\n",
+    "    display(summary[summary['label'] > 0])\n",
+    "    layout = infer_beta_layout(beta_shape, array.shape)\n",
+    "    print('h5py layout:', layout)\n",
+    "\n",
+    "prf_ctab = read_ctab(subject_paths['labels'] / 'prf-visualrois.mgz.ctab')\n",
+    "streams_ctab = read_ctab(subject_paths['labels'] / 'streams.mgz.ctab')\n",
+    "print('pRF visual ROI labels')\n",
+    "display(prf_ctab)\n",
+    "print('Streams labels')\n",
+    "display(streams_ctab)"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 5))\n",
+    "for ax, (name, array) in zip(axes, roi_arrays.items()):\n",
+    "    z = array.shape[2] // 2\n",
+    "    shown = np.where(array[:, :, z] > 0, array[:, :, z], np.nan)\n",
+    "    ax.imshow(np.rot90(shown), interpolation='nearest')\n",
+    "    ax.set_title(f'{name}: axial index {z}')\n",
+    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
+    "plt.tight_layout()"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 8. Safely read a small voxel sample\n",
+    "\n",
+    "For orientation, sample 300 `nsdgeneral` voxels and read all 720 events. The resulting matrix is `events × voxels`. This is tiny compared with the full four-dimensional array and already supports diagnostic plots and a toy RDM."
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "sample_betas, voxel_coordinates = extract_masked_betas(\n",
+    "    subject_paths['beta'], roi_arrays['nsdgeneral'], max_voxels=300, seed=2026\n",
+    ")\n",
+    "print('events × sampled voxels:', sample_betas.shape)\n",
+    "print('Units: percent signal change')\n",
+    "print(pd.Series(sample_betas.ravel()).describe(percentiles=[.01, .1, .5, .9, .99]))\n",
+    "\n",
+    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 4))\n",
+    "axes[0].hist(sample_betas.ravel(), bins=100)\n",
+    "axes[0].set(xlabel='percent signal change', ylabel='count', title='Sampled beta values')\n",
+    "axes[1].plot(sample_betas[:, 0], linewidth=0.8)\n",
+    "axes[1].set(xlabel='beta event index (Python)', ylabel='percent signal change', title='One sampled voxel across 720 events')\n",
+    "plt.tight_layout()"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "code",
+   "execution_count": null,
+   "metadata": {},
+   "outputs": [],
+   "source": [
+    "run_summaries = []\n",
+    "for row in run_table.itertuples(index=False):\n",
+    "    block = sample_betas[row.beta_start_python:row.beta_stop_python_exclusive]\n",
+    "    run_summaries.append({\n",
+    "        'run_name': row.run_name,\n",
+    "        'task': row.task,\n",
+    "        'stimulus_set': row.stimulus_set,\n",
+    "        'mean_beta': float(block.mean()),\n",
+    "        'mean_absolute_beta': float(np.abs(block).mean()),\n",
+    "        'spatial_sd': float(block.std(axis=1).mean()),\n",
+    "    })\n",
+    "run_summaries = pd.DataFrame(run_summaries)\n",
+    "display(run_summaries)\n",
+    "\n",
+    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(11, 4))\n",
+    "sns.barplot(data=run_summaries, x='run_name', y='mean_absolute_beta', hue='task', dodge=False, ax=ax)\n",
+    "ax.set_ylabel('mean |beta| in sampled nsdgeneral voxels')\n",
+    "ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)\n",
+    "plt.tight_layout()"
+   ]
+  },
+  {
+   "cell_type": "markdown",
+   "metadata": {},
+   "source": [
+    "## 9. What you should now understand\n",
+    "\n",
+    "1. A behavioral row describes a presented trial; a beta volume describes a modeled event. They are not globally one-to-one because attention has two modeled epochs.\n",
+    "2. Every beta is a three-dimensional response-amplitude map in subject-native 1.8-mm space.\n",
+    "3. The raw stored integer must be divided by 300 to recover percent signal change.\n",
+    "4. ROI masks select interpretable voxel subsets without registration because their spatial shapes match the beta grid.\n",
+    "5. Set A and set B give the cleanest first vision-versus-imagery comparison. Set C requires special care because concepts are paired with varying concrete images in vision.\n",
+    "\n",
+    "### Next notebook\n",
+    "\n",
+    "The next step should construct a verified event table for vision and imagery, average repeated beta patterns by subject × condition × target × ROI, and compute the first neural RDM. Do not begin CLIP/HOG feature extraction until that table passes alignment checks."
+   ]
+  }
+ ],
